---
import Heading from "@components/Heading.astro";
import HeadingLarge from "@components/HeadingLarge.astro";
import Text from "@components/Text.astro";
import View from "@components/View.astro";
import Group from "@components/Group.astro";
import { Layout } from "@layouts";
import Image from "@components/Image.astro";
import TextLink from "@components/TextLink.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Xero | Jonathon Toon | Software Designer, Product Leader"
  description="Jonathon Toon is a versatile software designer and product leader based in Aotearoa New Zealand."
  keywords="design, software, product, fractional, leadership, new zealand, aotearoa, technology, typescript, start ups, engineering, mentorship, coaching, adplist"
  twitterHandle="@jonathontoon"
  canonicalUrl="https://www.jonathontoon.com/"
  ogImage="/images/og-image.png"
>
  <Group>
    <HeadingLarge class="px-2">Xero</HeadingLarge>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Founded in New Zealand in 2006, Xero has grown into one of the world's
      leading online accounting platforms, helping over 3.5 million small
      business owners and their accountants manage their finances more easily.
      For many small businesses, Xero is the difference between staying on top
      of cash flow and scrambling through spreadsheets at tax time.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      In 2014, I joined Xero's newly formed mobile team in San Francisco as
      their first Mobile Product Designer for Payroll. Working across three
      continents, I helped establish our team culture and design direction
      alongside the Director of Product Design.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <View class="px-2">
      <View class="h-px w-full bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-700" />
    </View>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Heading class="px-2">Xero Me</Heading>
    <Text class="px-2">
      We inherited a product with two failed launches. Employees logged into
      outdated web interfaces to request time off, while managers forgot to
      check desktop computers for approvals. Working with a product manager,
      engineers, and another designer, we needed to understand what went wrong.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Replicating every desktop feature created unnecessary complexity.
      Employees wanted quick time-off requests. Managers needed mobile approval.
      We simplified around these core needs and launched at XeroCon.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      In addition to owning the end-to-end design for iOS, I wrote production
      code for a custom notification that instantly confirmed actions, elevating
      the craft and eliminating user uncertainty.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/xero-me-onboarding.png"
      alt="Employee onboarding flow introducing time-off request features."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Despite shipping pressure, I also partnered with a researcher to conduct
      some lean testing with customers. I designed test scenarios and prototypes
      while they handled recruitment, ensuring we delivered an experience that
      worked for real people.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Simply put, employees wanted to see the entire date range filled in, not
      just start and end dates. This simple visual change prevented scheduling
      conflicts and eliminated back-and-forth clarification.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/xero-me-request.png"
      alt="Simplified leave request form with calendar integration and visual feedback."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
    <Image
      src="/images/work/xero-me-edit-request.png"
      alt="Request editing with full date range selection based on user research insights."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Text class="px-2">
      We launched 10 months later across iOS and Android, announcing at XeroCon
      to enthusiastic response. Time-off requests that took days of email
      back-and-forth now happened instantly. Business owners could approve
      requests while traveling, and employees could submit requests the moment
      they thought of them.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      The success established Payroll on mobile as a core part of Xero's
      business, with Xero Me becoming one of Xero's <TextLink
        target="_blank"
        href="https://www.xero.com/nz/xero-me/">main offerings</TextLink
      >.
    </Text>
  </Group>
</Layout>
